Student Representatives

Members of the Student Representative Council work together with the administration in over 20 councils to ensure that the voice of the students is being heard. Issues and concerns are resolved through reports, and proposals to benefit the BYU-Idaho community. They also work to explain the "why" behind some of the most commonly misunderstood university policies. 8-12 Student Representatives are selected each semester.

Student Voice Coordinator & Program Managers

The student voice area administers a program of surveys, face to face contact, and focus groups in which over 4,000 students participate each semester. Working with student council representatives, they help gather information from students that university leaders need to make decisions. They also research topics to gather information, and measure issues unkown to administration. One student voice coordinator and two pragram managers oversee the student voice.

Student Representative Council Staff

As an organization, the SRC operates under the Student Support department at BYU-Idaho. The Student Support Coordinator acts as the SRC's advisor and works directly with the Student Representative Council members in administering the program.

1-2 Program Assistants work to manage the administrative work of the SRC including maintaining the SRC email accounts, Facebook page, and meeting records. They assist with the training and direction of SRC volunteers and with the production of reports, proposals, and the distribution of surveys.
